Accept‚ then, my Lord‚ in good part, this small work, such as it is 3 and, though it be not worthy of so great a Maecenati, take it under your patronage as a child of your own. The date of the volume to which this letter is prefixed is 1617, and Napier died upon the 4th of April in that same year. We learn from it the chronological order of the composition of all his published works. In the first place, he had long and laboriously wrought out—‘⁶ ὲ me longo tempore elaboratum„— his Canon of the Logarithms.
